          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-LI7"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 1.5 ns pulsed 4 MeV proton beam stroked thick",
                "lithium metal target and produced neutron energy",
                "continuum spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " NE218 scintillator. Bias levels were set to",
                "reject events corresponding to recoil protons of less",
                "than 0.4 MeV and greater than 6 MeV. Pulse shape",
                "discrimination against gamma-rays was also employed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight. Neutron flight paths from",
                "source to scatterer and from scatterer to detector",
                "were each 5 m. Data were averaged over 100 keV",
                "incident energy bins."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "No information"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Data corrected for multiple scattering, inelastic",
                "scattering, and background effects. Cross sections",
                "for 238U were corrected for inelastic scattering with",
                "the previously measured inelastic cross sections",
                "summarized by Lambropoulos. The magnitude of this",
                "correction at 1.5 deg ranged from about 10% at low",
                "energies to less than 1% at high energies. Use of a",
                "more recent set of evaluated cross sections would not",
                "substantially alter the results. Inelastic scattering",
                "corrections for lead were negligible."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " When these are quadratically combined with",
                "the effects of possible errors in alignment listed in",
                "table 1, the overall systematic uncertainties in",
                "cross section are approximately 7%, 11%, and 7% for",
                "the 0.5, 1.0, and 1.5 degree data, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": 8.0,
                "maximum_value": 13.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " When fluctuations in values of the",
                "cross sections stemming from the various corrections",
                "are quadratically combined with statistical standard",
                "deviations in the yields, uncertainties off 7% to 13%",
                "result."
              ]
            },
            {
